@vhf there pros/cons to using either method. for instance, if the urls are checked once a day, then the lists will be kept more or less up to date without any dependency on updates made to the repo to "trigger" a check.

Another benefit of checking regularly is that you can store the results in a database and make a better guess about why a link is bad. For example, if a particular link doesn't work (but only temporarily) you can make a determination on when to remove a link based on some reliability threshold that you get to set. But you'd only be able to make a good judgement if you had enough datapoints stored at regular intervals though.

